## 🔧 Agents = Model + Harness

Many people think AI systems are only about the model.

The reality is different.

The model is only one part of the system.

```text
Agent = Model + Harness
```

### Model

Provides reasoning and decision-making.

Examples:

- GPT
- Claude
- Gemini

### Harness

Everything surrounding the model.

Examples:

- Tools
- APIs
- Testing
- Monitoring
- Security
- Memory
- Evaluation systems

### Why It Matters

A powerful model without a strong harness is unreliable.

A well-designed harness often creates more value than upgrading to a larger model.

### Engineering Rule

```text
Strong Harness + Average Model
>
Strong Model + Weak Harness
```

---

## 🎼 Moving from Conductors to Orchestrators

The role of developers is changing.

### The Conductor

A conductor works directly with AI systems.

Responsibilities include:

- Prompting
- Reviewing outputs
- Correcting mistakes
- Guiding execution

The interaction is highly hands-on.

---

### The Orchestrator

An orchestrator manages entire systems of agents.

Responsibilities include:

- Workflow design
- Agent coordination
- Delegation strategies
- Context management
- Evaluation systems

The orchestrator focuses on outcomes rather than individual tasks.

### Evolution of the Developer

```text
Coder
 ↓
AI-Assisted Developer
 ↓
Conductor
 ↓
Orchestrator
```

This is one of the most important career transitions happening in software engineering today.

